SIMPLE: limpid
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Limpid
<hw>Lim"pid</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧m"p⟦icr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>limpidus</ets>; akin to Gr. <grk>la`mpein</grk> to shine: cf. F.
<ets>limpide</ets>. Cf. <er>Lamp</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Characterized by clearness or transparency; clear; <as>as, a
<ex>limpid</ex> stream</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Springs which were clear, fresh, and <qex>limpid</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Woodward.</qau></rj></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Clear and unambiguous; lucid; easy to understand; --
of speech and writing; <as>as, <ex>limpid</ex> prose</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Calm, untroubled, and without worry;
serene.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Clear; transparent; pellucid; lucid; pure;
crystal; translucent; bright.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Limpidity</ent>⟦br⟧
